<doc id="1220706" wikidata="Q3106790" url="?curid=1220706" title="Ginnosuke Tanaka">
<text>is credited with the introduction of rugby to Japan. He was educated at the Leys School in Cambridge and then Trinity Hall, a college of Cambridge University. He introduced rugby to students at Keio University, in 1899, with the help of Edward Bramwell Clarke. Later, he pursued a career in banking.

